article.headline: Workman scores 18, Jacksonville takes down Campbell 62-48

images.name: Bryce Workman gets the and-1 to fall
images.caption: Bryce Workman gets the and-1 to fall

article.linkText: Workman scores 18, Jacksonville takes down Campbell 62-48
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- — Bryce Workman's 18 points helped Jacksonville defeat Campbell 62-48 on Wednesday night. Workman added 11 rebounds for the Dolphins (5-2). Robert McCray scored 13 points while shooting 4 for 8 (0 for 4 from 3-point range) and 5 of 5 from the free throw line. Jarius Cook and Gyasi Powell both had 10 points. The Fighting Camels (2-5) were led by Anthony Dell'Orso, who recorded 19 points, six rebounds and two steals. Laurynas Vaistaras added nine points for Campbell. NEXT UP Both teams play on Saturday. Jacksonville visits Georgia Southern and Campbell hosts Southern Virginia. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
